{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.22",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 22 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:2",
      "text": "“ Can a man be profitable to God? Surely he who is wise is profitable to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:3",
      "text": "Is it any pleasure to the Almighty that you are righteous? Or does it benefit him that you make your ways perfect?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:4",
      "text": "Is it for your piety that he reproves you, that he enters with you into judgment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:5",
      "text": "Isn’t your wickedness great? Neither is there any end to your iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:6",
      "text": "For you have taken pledges from your brother for nothing, and stripped the naked of their clothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:7",
      "text": "You haven’t given water to the weary to drink, and you have withheld bread from the hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:8",
      "text": "But as for the mighty man, he had the earth. The honorable man, he lived in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:9",
      "text": "You have sent widows away empty, and the arms of the fatherless have been broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:10",
      "text": "Therefore snares are around you. Sudden fear troubles you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:11",
      "text": "or darkness, so that you can not see, and floods of waters cover you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:12",
      "text": "“Isn’t God in the heights of heaven? See the height of the stars, how high they are!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:13",
      "text": "You say, ‘ What does God know? Can he judge through the thick darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:14",
      "text": "Thick clouds are a covering to him, so that he doesn’t see. He walks on the vault of the sky.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:15",
      "text": "Will you keep the old way, which wicked men have trodden,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:16",
      "text": "who were snatched away before their time, whose foundation was poured out as a stream,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:17",
      "text": "who said to God, ‘ Depart from us!’ and, ‘ What can the Almighty do for us?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:18",
      "text": "Yet he filled their houses with good things, but the counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:19",
      "text": "The righteous see it, and are glad. The innocent ridicule them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:20",
      "text": "saying, ‘ Surely those who rose up against us are cut off. The fire has consumed their remnant.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:21",
      "text": "“ Acquaint yourself with him now, and be at peace. By it, good will come to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:22",
      "text": "Please receive instruction from his mouth, and lay up his words in your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:23",
      "text": "If you return to the Almighty, you will be built up, if you put away unrighteousness far from your tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:24",
      "text": "Lay your treasure in the dust, the gold of Ophir among the stones of the brooks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:25",
      "text": "The Almighty will be your treasure, and precious silver to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:26",
      "text": "For then you will delight yourself in the Almighty, and will lift up your face to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:27",
      "text": "You will make your prayer to him, and he will hear you. You will pay your vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:28",
      "text": "You will also decree a thing, and it will be established to you. Light will shine on your ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:29",
      "text": "When they cast down, you will say, ‘ be lifted up.’ He will save the humble person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.22.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:30",
      "text": "He will even deliver him who is not innocent. Yes, he will be delivered through the cleanness of your hands.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
